4.72	Zia_International_Airport	Shahjalal International Airport	Hazrat Shahjalal International Airport , formerly Zia International Airport, is the largest airport in Bangladesh. It is located in the capital Dhaka and started operations in 1980, taking over as the country's sole international airport from Tejgaon Airport. It is the home base and hub of all Bangladeshi airlines, including Biman Bangladesh Airlines, GMG Airlines, and United Airways.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/02/Hazrat_Shahjalal_International_Airport.jpg/250px-Hazrat_Shahjalal_International_Airport.jpg
